  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is cache-miss-heavy random lookup overhead (Category E): each filtered adsh currently triggers repeated binary searches over cache-exceeding triple-entry arrays. I added persistent compact storage extensions mapping adsh to contiguous triple-entry spans for both pre and num indexes, then revised the plan to drive joins via direct range lookups and in-range merge processing so main-scan work stays sequential and avoids high-latency random probes.",
